08/03/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Foreign Minister Solomon Passy says parliament will put off ratification of the document endorsing the country's entry into NATO, probably until next week.
Ratification was planned for Thursday (11 March);
Passy blames the delay on the ongoing no-confidence vote against the cabinet.
In other news, Deputy Prime Minister Lidia Shouleva has just returned from a trip to the United States.
The focus of her visit was post-war Iraq's recovery and reconstruction.
According to Shouleva, Bulgarian companies will be exporting arms and ammunition to the future Iraqi Army.
(Standart, Sega, BTA - 08/03/04)
